Your page is already close. The main problems are duplicate CSS rules, inconsistent font-family names, and one incorrect Open Sans path.

## 1. Fix the font declarations

One of your current paths contains an extra `/static/`:

```css
url('../fonts/OpenSans/.woff2/static/OpenSans-Light.woff2')
```

That should be:

```css
url('../fonts/OpenSans/.woff2/OpenSans-Light.woff2')
```

Use one font family name per font family and let `font-weight` choose the file:

```css
@font-face {
    font-family: 'Ubuntu';
    src: url('../fonts/Ubuntu/.woff2/Ubuntu-Light.woff2') format('woff2');
    font-weight: 300;
    font-style: normal;
    font-display: swap;
}

@font-face {
    font-family: 'Ubuntu';
    src: url('../fonts/Ubuntu/.woff2/Ubuntu-Bold.woff2') format('woff2');
    font-weight: 700;
    font-style: normal;
    font-display: swap;
}

@font-face {
    font-family: 'Open Sans';
    src: url('../fonts/OpenSans/.woff2/OpenSans-Light.woff2') format('woff2');
    font-weight: 300;
    font-style: normal;
    font-display: swap;
}

@font-face {
    font-family: 'Open Sans';
    src: url('../fonts/OpenSans/.woff2/OpenSans-Medium.woff2') format('woff2');
    font-weight: 500;
    font-style: normal;
    font-display: swap;
}

@font-face {
    font-family: 'Open Sans';
    src: url('../fonts/OpenSans/.woff2/OpenSans-Bold.woff2') format('woff2');
    font-weight: 700;
    font-style: normal;
    font-display: swap;
}
```

Then stop using these mixed names:

```css
UbuntuBold
UbuntuLight
OpenSansLight
OpenSansCustom
```

Use only:

```css
font-family: 'Ubuntu', Arial, sans-serif;
```

or:

```css
font-family: 'Open Sans', Arial, sans-serif;
```

