## 8. Improve the desktop grid proportions

Your current right side uses `42vw`, which makes the illustration quite large. That may be intentional, but to better match the design:

```css
.content-container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(420px, 42vw);
    min-height: calc(100vh - 96px);
    align-items: stretch;
}
```

The right panel itself can stay:

```css
.right-illustration {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    min-height: calc(100vh - 96px);
    overflow: hidden;
    border-top-left-radius: 40px;
    background: var(--color-green-dark);
}
```

